OL,3,CRyanair to boost free cabin baggage
OL,4,Csize ahead of the summer holidays
OL,6,FEurope's biggest low-cost airline,
OL,7,FRyanair, has said it will increase its
OL,8,Ffree cabin luggage allowance, set to
OL,9,Fbe carried out in the coming weeks.
OL,11,FThe budget air carrier currently
OL,12,Fallows a "personal bag" measuring 40 x
OL,13,F25 x 25cm, equating to a volume of 20
OL,14,Flitres at no extra cost.
OL,16,FThe new volume will increase to 24
OL,17,Flitres while dimensions will change to
OL,18,F40 x 30 x 20cm, allowing holidaymakers
OL,19,Fto pack a little more.
