OL,3,CRyanair to boost free cabin baggage
OL,4,Csize ahead of the summer holidays
OL,6,FThe change comes after MEPs voted last
OL,7,Fmonth for all airlines to allow
OL,8,Fpassengers to carry both a personal
OL,9,Fitem and one small hand luggage on
OL,10,Fboard for free, which Ryanair, easyJet
OL,11,Fand Wizz Air strongly opposed because
OL,12,Fof impracticality.
OL,14,FThe European Parliament said:
OL,15,F"Passengers should have a right to
OL,16,Fcarry on board one personal item, such
OL,17,Fas a handbag, backpack or laptop
OL,18,F(maximum dimensions of 40x30x15 cm),
OL,19,Fand one small hand luggage (maximum
OL,20,Fdimensions of 100 cm and 7 kg) without
OL,21,Fan additional fee."
